# Code Quality Rules
- Use async/await instead of .then() chains
- Handle errors explicitly, don't silently fail
- Use meaningful variable and function names
- Add JSDoc comments for complex functions and public APIs
- Avoid magic numbers and strings - use constants or enums
- Use early returns to reduce nesting
- Prefer const over let, avoid var
- Use optional chaining (?.) and nullish coalescing (??) when appropriate
- Keep functions small and focused
- Use TypeScript strict mode features (no any unless necessary)
- Prefer interfaces over type aliases for object shapes
- Use enums or const objects for fixed sets of values
